      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "OCTOBER ROX (8) resumes and has shown enough to say this is winnable if he's presented forward as expected. Broke her Maiden with an easy win here and raced in stronger than this following. Maps well, and Staples has been with him all along. GLOBAL TRIP (3) ran a strong third over 1200m at Pinjarra Scarpside two runs back then was below his best last time over 1300m in tough company at Ascot. Peaks and this is a winnable assignment. ZAC LUVS TO FLY (4) has a moderate winning strike-rate but performed well last time beaten 2.5 lengths over 1400m at Ascot. Led in that and is likely to push forward again. Has a 2kg claim and he can make the finish. GOOD VIBES (7) resumes and ran his best race placing here last time. Has trialled x2 solidly at Belmont and the 3kg claim brings her into it.",
